    </mj-section>
    <mj-section background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="
              font-size: 24px; 
              line-height: 1.2; 
              font-weight: 400;
              margin-top: 2px !important; 
            ">El Salvador's Bukele rules out return</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/kilmar-abrego-garcia-el-salvador-prison-deportation-case.png" alt="Kilmar Ábrego García was sent to a prison in El Salvador" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Kilmar Ábrego García was sent to a prison in El Salvador. Credits: Reuters
            </i></p>
        </mj-text>
        
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Trump’s administration is put in a tough spot. The US Supreme Court ruled that <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-16-04-2025-h1-1-kilmar-abrego-garcia?source=website" target="_blank">Kilmar Ábrego García</a>, one of the 238 Venezuelans and 23 Salvadorans deported to El Salvador, is not a gang member. However, El Salvador President Nayib Bukele said he <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-16-04-2025-h1-2-would-not-return?source=website" target="_blank">would not return</a> him.<p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5;filter:blur(5px);">
        Lawyers claim that his case was an issue of foreign policy and outside the courts' control. The court had ordered officials to provide a daily update on the steps taken to bring him back. While the US admits the deportation was an “administrative error,” they still claim that he’s a gang member, which his lawyer denies.</p>

        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-spacer height="15px"></mj-spacer>
